race.comment: STEEL MOVE (9) has been thereabouts without winning, the most recent effort a third at Bendigo over 1100m when he was beaten 2 lengths. Settles back early but winds up late. Will prove hard to hold out. ATTACHMENTS (10) kept coming only to just miss when fresh from a spell last start over 1200m at Mornington. Will take a lot from that hitout. Hard to beat in this suitable race. LAKE FOREST (3) came home strongly last start to finish second, beaten 1.3 lengths, over 1100m at Bendigo. Has a strong record at this journey with two wins and a placing from four starts and should be in the finish. MR ASSERTIVE (16) broke through last start and could go on with it.
